== Views ==
Economically, Robertson has been described as an [[underconsumptionist]], and he gave an early form, perhaps the earliest formal statement, of the [[paradox of thrift]] in his 1892 book ''The Fallacy of Saving.''<ref>{{cite book
|first=John M.
|last=Robertson
|authorlink=J. M. Robertson
|title=The Fallacy of Saving
|year=1892
|url=https://archive.org/stream/fallacyofsavings00robe/fallacyofsavings00robe_djvu.txt
}}</ref><ref name="neglect">{{cite journal
|title=A Neglected Early Statement the Paradox of Thrift
|first1=Robert T.
|last1=Nash
|first2=William P.
|last2=Gramm
|journal=History of Political Economy
