{{about|a British magazine|the American version|UFO Magazine}} {{notability|date=April 2016}} <!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Ufomag uk v11n1.jpg|right|thumb|Cover of ''UFO Magazine'''s March/April 1992 issue]] -->'''''UFO Magazine''''' was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[magazine]] devoted to the subject of [[unidentified flying object]]s (UFOs) and [[extraterrestrial life]]. It was founded in 1981 by brothers [[Graham Birdsall|Graham]] and [[Mark Birdsall]] of [[Leeds]], [[Yorkshire]].<ref name="observer">Townsend, Mark "[https://www.theguardian.com/media/2004/mar/14/pressandpublishing.uknews UFO spies vanish into black hole]", [[The Observer]], March 14, 2004</ref> The magazine was one of the success stories of [[ufology]], with an international reputation for quality and a peak circulation of 35,000.<ref name="observer" /><ref name="ind">Herbert, Ian "[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/this-britain/ufospotters-give-up-hunt-for-flying-saucers-502194.html UFO-spotters give up hunt for flying saucers]", [[The Independent]], 10 August 2005</ref>
Graham Birdsall died from a brain haemorrhage on September 19, 2003. He left behind his wife Christine, daughters Helen and Louise, granddaughter Katy, brother Mark and son-in-law Russel.<ref>{{cite web|title=Graham W. Birdsall - Editor UFO Magazine UK 1954 - 2003|url=http://www.fsr.org.uk/GBirdsall.htm|work=Flying Saucer Review|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref> <ref>Jeeves, Paul "[http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/UFO-hunters-back-in-Leeds.1137938.jp UFO hunters back in Leeds...]", Yorkshire Evening Post</ref> The editor's job was taken over for a few months by Graham's son-in-law [[Russel Callaghan]], but ''UFO Magazine'' eventually ceased publication in March 2004.<ref name="observer" />
The void left by ''UFO Magazine'' has been filled to some extent by the newly produced [[UFO Data]] magazine referred to as the 'UFO Data Report'<ref>[http://www.rendlesham-incident.co.uk/forum/viewtopic.php?t=9 Rendlesham Discussion :: View topic - New UFO Magazine - UFOdata.co.uk]</ref> and [[Gary Heseltine]]'s [[UFO Monthly Magazine]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.alienexistence.com/store/16SEPTEMBER2005.pdf |title=Did a ufo crash into the troodos mountains of cyprus in 1973? - UFOmonthly.com }}&nbsp;{{small|(2.17&nbsp;MB)}}</ref>
